05/05/2003
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Zagreb will host a regional summit of presidents' wives in Central and East Europe later this week, promoting efforts at early breast cancer diagnosis. 
Milka Mesic, the wife of President Stipe Mesic, is chairwoman of the national committee for public education on early diagnosis. 
The first ladies of the United Kingdom, the United States and Australia have sent letters of support to the forum. 
Organisers say 12 out of 19 participants have accepted the invitations so far. 
(HINA - 04/05/03)
